---
const stats = [
  { value: '5+', label: 'Years Experience' },
  { value: '10+', label: 'Projects Shipped' },
  { value: '50%', label: 'Engagement Increase' },
  { value: '40%', label: 'SEO Rankings Boost' },
];
---
<section id="about">
  <section class="about-inner section-inner">
    <h2 class="section-heading" data-aos="fade-up">About Me</h2>
    <div class="about-inner__content" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100">
      <p>
        I'm a <strong>full-stack, frontend, backend, and mobile developer
        based in Nairobi, Kenya</strong>, with <strong>5+ years</strong> of
        experience across startups and SaaS companies. I build production-grade
        <strong>React, Next.js, Node.js, Go, and Flutter</strong> applications.
        Teams I've led have shipped products that achieved a
        <strong>40% increase in SEO rankings</strong>,
        <strong>33% improvement in user retention</strong>, and
        <strong>50% rise in user engagement</strong>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Selected work includes <strong>Pocket of Paradise</strong> (luxury
        travel platform), <strong>Yeshara</strong> (CMA-approved real-estate
        blockchain), <strong>Mamlaka Hub</strong> (agentic AI fintech),
        <strong>TripHoppa</strong> (peer-to-peer parcel shipping with a Flutter
        mobile app), and <strong>Almaza</strong> (fintech virtual cards on the
        App Store). My specialties: end-to-end web and mobile development, API
        design, and Kenyan payment integrations — <strong>MPESA, Pesapal,
        and Flutterwave</strong>.
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm an active member of the Nairobi developer community and regularly
        attend Nairobi tech meetups (JavaScript, GDG Nairobi, Flutter Nairobi).
        Available for hire across Nairobi and remotely worldwide.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="about-inner__stats" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="200">
      {stats.map((stat) => (
        <div class="stat">
          <span class="stat__number">{stat.value}</span>
          <span class="stat__label">{stat.label}</span>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>
</section>
